The key studies include ADA, LDH, and Gene Xpe as they help diagnose tuberculosis by differentiating it from other causes; whereas albumin testing has no specific utility in directly confirming or ruling out TB infection based on its function alone. \boxed{D}

The summary captures only the essential information regarding why each test might be used but focuses particularly on excluding one due to lack of specificity related to diagnosis over nutrition assessment. ```plaintext
Key studies like ADA, LDH, and Gene Xpe aid in diagnosing TB, while albumin serves more generally for assessing protein levels rather than identifying TB-specifically. Thus, sending just an albumin level would exclude targeted diagnostics crucial for distinguishing TB from other conditions causing pleural effusion.\boxed{D}
``` This version maintains clarity around critical aspects without extraneous details about broader functions unrelated to differential diagnoses.

